-- Citi to keep capital markets tie with Nikko Cordial
-- 
-- Fri May 1, 2009 5:01am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/05/01/us-citigroup-japan-nikko-sb-idUSTRE54026O20090501

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Citigroup will keep its ties with Japanese broker Nikko Cordial in capital markets after selling Nikko Cordial to Sumitomo Mitsui Financial Group (SMFG), Citigroup Vice Chairman Stephen Volk said. 

 At the same news conference, Masayuki Oku, CEO of SMFG's core unit Sumitomo Mitsui Banking Corp, said the bank wants to discuss a three-way alliance with Citigroup and Daiwa Securities following the deal. SMFG and Daiwa Securities have an investment banking joint venture, Daiwa SMBC Securities. (Reporting by  David Dolan  and  Junko Fujita )